    "question_id" : 4427608,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use this function to get resource ID.</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static int getResourceId(String pVariableName, String pResourcename, String pPackageName) \n{\n    try {\n        return getResources().getIdentifier(pVariableName, pResourcename, pPackageName);\n    } catch (Exception e) {\n        e.printStackTrace();\n        return -1;\n    } \n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>So if you want to get for <strong>drawable</strong> call function like this</p>\n\n<pre><code>getResourceId(\"myIcon\", \"drawable\", getPackageName());\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>and for string you can call it like this</p>\n\n<pre><code>getResourceId(\"myAppName\", \"string\", getPackageName());\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://daniel-codes.blogspot.com/2009/12/dynamically-retrieving-resources-in.html\">Read this</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
