    "creation_date" : 1467196910,
    "answer_id" : 38097226,
    "question_id" : 4427608,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>For getting Drawable id from String resource name I am using this code:</p>\n\n<pre><code>private int getResId(String resName) {\n    int defId = -1;\n    try {\n        Field f = R.drawable.class.getDeclaredField(resName);\n        Field def = R.drawable.class.getDeclaredField(\"transparent_flag\");\n        defId = def.getInt(null);\n        return f.getInt(null);\n    } catch (NoSuchFieldException | IllegalAccessException e) {\n        return defId;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
